President Joe Biden has announced his intent to nominate four individuals for key roles promoting U.S. foreign policy. The nominees are John R. Bass for Under Secretary of State for Management, David L. Cohen for Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary to Canada, Jamie L. Harpootlian for Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary to the Republic of Slovenia, and Victoria Reggie Kennedy for Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary to the Republic of Austria.

John R. Bass is a career member of the Senior Foreign Service and has previously served as Ambassador to Afghanistan, Turkey, and Georgia. He has also focused on combating terrorism and instability in Iraq, Syria, and Southwest Asia.

David L. Cohen is currently a Senior Advisor at Comcast Corporation and has a background in corporate communications, legal affairs, and government and regulatory affairs. He has also served as Chief of Staff to the Mayor of Philadelphia and has been involved in various nonprofit boards and organizations.

Jamie L. Harpootlian is an attorney who has worked on federal litigation matters and served as a court-appointed Special Master. She has also provided legal advice to the United States District Court for the Eastern District of Louisiana. Harpootlian is involved in supporting nonprofit groups in areas such as the environment, arts, and historic resources.

Victoria Reggie Kennedy is a Senior Counsel at Greenberg Traurig LLP and is the president of the board and co-founder of the Edward M. Kennedy Institute for the United States Senate. She has a background in corporate and securities law and has received numerous awards for her civic and charitable activities. Kennedy is also an advocate for gun safety.

These nominations reflect President Biden's commitment to assembling a diverse and experienced team to advance U.S. foreign policy goals.